[size=%sizeh1%][b]About[/b][/size]
With this mod you're able to display a ghost image of a schematic file inside Minecraft to rebuild a structure or export any part of your world (or a server's world) into a schematic file. You're able to export parts of your world, too!


[size=%sizeh1%][b]Recommendations[/b][/size][spoiler]
The following is small compilation of mods that I recommend using. They are not mandatory, but they may make things easier for you.
[list]
[*][url=http://openeye.openmods.info/download]OpenEye[/url]
Automatic crash reporting, the crash reports can be found [url=http://openeye.openmods.info/crashes]here[/url]. It's an awesome mod that helps mod developers fix crashes way faster.
[*][url=http://www.minecraftforum.net/forums/t/2091981-version-checker]Dynious' Version Checker[/url]
LunatriusCore's update notifications will be replaced with an entry in Version Checker if the mod is installed.
[/list]
[/spoiler]


[size=%sizeh1%][b]FAQ, Help, Crash Reports[/b][/size][list]
[*][url=https://github.com/Lunatrius/Schematica/wiki]Wiki[/url]
[*][url=https://github.com/Lunatrius/Schematica/wiki/Frequently-Asked-Questions]Wiki ~ FAQ[/url]
[/list]
Before reporting a bug, [b]READ[/b] the [b]FAQ[/b]. I won't be replying to posts reporting bugs/issues in the FAQ that can be fixed by the user. If I ignore you you may consider reading the FAQ.[numlist]
[*]Make sure you use the [b]latest[/b] version of the mod.
[i]Bugs are usually fixed within a few days of reporting the bug.[/i]
[*]Upload (copy&paste) [b].minecraft/logs/[u]fml-client-latest.log[/u][/b] to [url=https://gist.github.com/]https://gist.github.com/[/url] and add the link to it to the post.
[i]Note: if the crash is on the server upload fml-server-latest.log instead.[/i]
[*]Describe what you were doing when the mod crashed. The more details, the easier for me to fix it as soon as possible. If something doesn't look right, add screenshots or optionally a video if you can.
[/numlist]
